The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Tuesday, April 27, 2004 				 Cinematic impressions
																								M F Husains venture into films has been attempts to portray the female sex in its myriad forms and hues from divine to worldly, from bashful to playful, from banal to inspirational. Celebrating the release of his latest film, Meenaxi: Tale of 3 Cities, Galerie 88 hosts an exhibition of paintings by the artist, based on the film. The exhibition provides an insight into the thoughts, passions and emotions that stirred Husains mind while he was making the film. Whether depicted as the mysterious perfume trader of Hyderabad, the exotic desert bloom of Jaisalmer or the orphaned Maria of Prague, the different personae that the protagonist Meenaxi assumes in the film are brilliantly represented in the paintings, offering us fresh perspectives on the relationship between the film and painting media.																								Event: An exhibition of paintings by MF Husain based on the film, Meenaxi: Tale of 3 Cities																								When: Till April 30; 3 pm - 7 pm																								Where: Galerie 88, 28B Shakespeare Sarani
